template: Create port scanning pattern targeting web servers
attack_code:
A port scanning pattern for targeting web servers is:

1. TCP Port Scan:
   - 23 (HTTP)
   - 80 (HTTP)
   - 443 (HTTPS)
2. Nmap Scan:
   - Hostname or IP address of web server (e.g. www.example.com)
   - Port range from 2000 to 65534 (inclusive)
   - Wait time: 10 seconds
   - Scan every x seconds (default is 5)
3. Burp Suite Proxy:
   - Hostname or IP address of web server (e.g. www.example.com)
   - Port range from 80 to 65534 (inclusive)
   - Wait time: 10 seconds

Use this port scanning pattern for validating the security vulnerabilities of web servers and to identify any unauthorized access to their network.
